<2ND_LINE>BC-Argentina-Plane, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0657,0238</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Jetliner Crashes In Argentina, At Least 21 Feared Dead</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 4 grafs to UPDATE with plane crashing at 9:50 a.m.
into a plantation. Pickup 4th graf pvs, ``There were...''</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A DC-9 jetliner carrying at least
21 people crashed Sunday while trying to land at a fogbound airport
in northeastern Argentina, authorities said. There were no
immediate reports of survivors.
   According to the government news agency Telam, at least 15
passengers and a crew of six were on board the Austral airlines
jet, which left Buenos Aires' airport at 7 a.m. and stopped at the
northern river port of Resistencia.
   Local news and radio reports said the plane then headed north
and crashed at 9:50 a.m. into a plantation three miles short of the
Posadas airport while trying to land there in heavy fog.
   Posadas, the capital of Misiones Province, is 700 miles
northeast of Buenos Aires and across the Parana River from the
Paraguayan city of Encarnacion.
   There were unconfirmed reports the jetliner was on fire moments
before it crashed. Firefighters who rushed to the scene in the
semi-tropical north of Argentina said it appeared unlikely there
were any survivors, Telam said.
   Austral is a private carrier purchased last year from the state
that competes with the government carrier Aerolineas Argentinas on
domestic routes across Argentina, the world's eighth-largest
country geographically.
</TEXT>
