<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--MozambiqueRebels     06-12 0139</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Mozambique Rebels,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Report: Mozambique Rebels Kill Two Zimbabwe Villagers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mozambican rebels shot and killed a
mother and her son in a remote village in northeastern Zimbabwe, a
newspaper said Sunday.
   The attack was the second cross-border raid by Mozambique
National Resistance geurrillas into Zimbabwe's Mount Darwin area in
four weeks, said the Sunday Mail, which is published in Harare by
the state-owned Mass Media Trust.
   It said the incident happened several days ago and was confirmed
by Harare police Saturday. Police identified the dead as Mativenga
Nyarugwe and her 4-year-old son, Karorado.
   The right-wing Mozambique National Resistance, also known by its
Portuguese acronym RENAMO, has been fighting since 1977 to topple
Mozambique's Marxist government. RENAMO rebels have have mounted
numerous raids into Zimbabwe during the past year, mainly to steal
food and supplies.
</TEXT>
