<1ST_LINE>r i AM-ErrantSpear     06-12 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Errant Spear,0167</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Hurls Spear At Bandits, Kills Wife</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A farmer lying in wait for a gang of
robbers hurled a spear from his hideout and accidentally killed one
of his two wives, police said Sunday.
   Joseph Sikuku heard noises from where he hid outside his village
of Indangalaisa on Friday night, thought it was a gang that had
robbed his neighbors and tossed the spear, police said.
   His wife, Paustsina Nambutie, was hidden in some bushes nearby
and was fatally wounded.
   Police said they were hunting the eight-man gang that had robbed
four families in the village early that evening.
   Sikuku, fearing he might become a victim of the gang, woke his
two wives and their children and told them to hide in a nearby
cornfield, police said.
   He took cover armed with a spear. He realized he had killed his
wife when he left his hideout to inspect the body of his victim,
police said.
</TEXT>
