<1ST_LINE>r i AM--Soviet-ShipFire     06-12 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM--Soviet-Ship Fire,0160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soviet Probe Says Ship Fire Caused by Electric Heaters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Passengers using unauthorized electric heaters
caused a fire that swept through a Soviet cruise ship and killed 11
people, a Soviet investigation has concluded.
   The official Tass news agency said a Soviet Ministry of Merchant
Marine commission had traced the source of last month's fire in
Japan's Osaka Bay.
   ``The fire was due to passengers in cabin 346 using household
electric heaters contrary to regulations,'' Tass quoted commission
chairman Oleg Savin as saying.
   In its dispatch Friday, Tass did not say whether the passengers
who set up the heaters aboard the 4,870-ton Priamurye were among
the dead or whether legal action was being considered. But it said
a prosecutor's office was conducting its own probe, indicating
legal action is likely.
   Japanese investigators said shortly after the May 17-18 fire
that it may have been caused by a cigarette in a passenger cabin.
</TEXT>
