<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--France-Spelunker     06-12 0154</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--France-Spelunker,0159</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>British Spelunker's Body Found in Cave</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRENOBLE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The body of a young British spelunker
missing since August was found Sunday in a cave near Grenoble,
officials said.
   Alex Pritcher, 17, disappeared Aug. 7 after he became separated
from 20 other young cave explorers. All were from Manchester,
England.
   His companions reported him missing after he failed to appear at
a meeting point outside the cave.
   For more than a week, a team of 170 French rescue workers
searched inside and around the outside of the cave without finding
Pritcher.
   On Sunday, a team of first-aid workers training in cave rescues
discovered him at the bottom of a shaft near a network of chasms
known as the Shepherd's Pit, according to local police officials.
   The pit plunges to a depth of 3,765 feet. Authorities said
Pritcher probably died after being struck on the head and shoulders
by falling rocks.
</TEXT>
