<1ST_LINE>r a AM-PuertoRicanDay     06-12 0136</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Puerto Rican Day,0138</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Puerto Rican Day Parade Draws 1.5 Million People</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 1.5 million people turned out Sunday
to watch the 30th Puerto Rican Day Parade, the city's
second-largest parade.
   More than 75 floats and 50 bands, some of which came from Puerto
Rico, participated in the parade, which proceeded up Fifth Avenue.
Some streets were closed to traffic for the afternoon. Police
reported no major problems.
   The parade, under a near cloudless sky and in warm temperatures,
drew many of the city's 1.1 million Puerto Ricans.
   It featured the theme ``Yes to school and no to drugs.''
   Entertainer Jose Feliciano said at the parade: ``I feel great to
support our people, but the most important thing of all is that I'm
proud to be a Puerto Rican American.''
</TEXT>
